We collect information about your previous search queries, activities, site or app visits, demographic information, and location through Google to serve ads optimized for individual users. We provide information such as IP addresses, device-specific information, and application usage events to third-party solutions such as Firebase, Flurry, and Fabric for quality control, determining minimum device requirements, compatibility and interoperability of KineMaster with other apps. The information provided will not be used for any purpose other than improving the quality of the app.\10\10See the following links for detailed privacy policies below.\10\'FireBase Privacy Policy\'\10\'Flurry Privacy Policy\'\10\'Fabric Privacy Policy\'\10\10Not consenting to this data use will not restrict the use of this feature, however some features may be limited. We collect personal information, including your email address and name to create your KineMaster account.\10\10Collected email addresses and names are used for user identification, and can be used to transfer information such as app updates, new items etc. as needed.\10\10We also collect device identifiers, item downloads, and purchase information that occurs when you use KineMaster. Device identifiers are used for the purpose of limiting the number of available terminals for each user. Item download and purchase information is used for checking purchase details, refunding items, and redownloading items. The collected data will not be used in outside of the purposes mentioned above. Information is collected and used while the account is in use. For more information, please refer to our Privacy Policy.\10\10If you do not agree to these terms, you will not be able to create a user account. If you do not create a user account, you will be able to use the app as normal, however some features will be limited.\10\10Do you agree to the provision and use of your personal information to create an account?

In order to provide voice recording functionality, KineMaster needs to be able to access your device\'s microphone. This is optional, but you must allow permission if you want to perform voice recording directly in KineMaster.
You can enable microphone access for KineMaster under Apps in your device settings.

In order to provide video recording functionality, KineMaster needs to be able to access your device\'s camera and microphone for recording video and audio. This is optional (you can use another app for camcording instead) but you must allow permission if you want to perform camcording directly in KineMaster.
You can enable camera and microphone access for KineMaster under Apps in your device settings.

In order to take photos, KineMaster needs to be able to access your device\'s camera. This is optional (you can use another app to take photos instead) but you must allow permission if you want to take photos directly in KineMaster.
You can enable camera access for KineMaster under Apps in your device settings.
Allow KineMaster to access Phone Calls for Ads and In_App Billing?
